# AetherOps Phase 2: Full-Stack Integration & AI Core

Transition the AetherOps dashboard from local mock data to a live full-stack app backed by Supabase (DB + Realtime) and OpenAI (GPT-based AI analysis). This covers 4 steps: Supabase wiring, ingestion route, VAPT scanner route, and UI execution wiring.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Environment Variables** — The following must be set in a `.env.local` file at the project root before running:
> ```env
> NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=<your-supabase-project-url>
> NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<your-supabase-anon-key>
> SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=<your-service-role-key>
> OPENAI_API_KEY=<your-openai-api-key>
> ```
> The `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` is needed server-side (API routes) to bypass RLS. The `OPENAI_API_KEY` is never exposed to the client.

> [!WARNING]
> **Schema Update** — The existing `deals` table needs two new columns (`compliance_status` and `ai_summary`) to support the `/api/ingest` and `/api/scan` routes. A migration SQL file will be provided.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **npm install** — The `openai` package will be added as a new dependency.

